14/03/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski acknowledged on Thursday (March 13th) that the country is in the grip of a serious political crisis at a significant moment in history. "We are just 20 days from the NATO summit in Bucharest, where we expect a membership invitation, as well as in the most delicate stage of name talks with Greece," he said, urged ruling coalition parties to seek compromise. On Wednesday, the Democratic Party of Albanians announced plans to leave the ruling coalition, saying its requests had been ignored. (Dnevnik - 14/03/08; MIA, Makfax, A1 TV, MRT - 13/03/08)
